        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">CHISEL — 11 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">C=3, H=4, I=1, S=1, E=1, L=1 · 6 letters · CH combo</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">A cutting tool with a bevelled blade. CHISEL's CH opening (7pts from two tiles) makes it efficient — the remaining 4 letters are all 1-pointers that appear frequently on the board. Hooks to CHISELS (12pts) and CHISELLED.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🪵 DOWEL</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">9 pts · D=2, O=1, W=4, E=1, L=1 · Wooden pin</p></div>
