      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Woodwork Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">CHISEL targets the CH pair:</span> When you draw C and H together, CHISEL is a reliable 6-letter play. The remaining tiles (I, S, E, L) are the four most common letters in the bag — you'll often have them available.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">DOWEL burns the W tile:</span> W (4pts) is notoriously hard to place. DOWEL uses it with four common 1-2 point tiles, guaranteeing 9 points and clearing the W from your rack for better draws.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">CLAMP stacks three 3-pointers:</span> C (3pts), M (3pts), and P (3pts) in one 5-letter word. That's 9 points from three consonants plus 2 from A and L. On a DWS, CLAMP hits 22 points.</p></div>
      </div>
